"Abstract False invoices have featured prominently in a number of recent investigations. The fraudster typically creates false invoices on his workstation or laptop. Many of the false invoices that I have seen, frankly, looked false — they were produced in a careless, childlike, seemingly casual way, without any concerted attempt to convey authenticity 1 . And yet, time and time again, these crude deceptions, once initialled by the authorized approver, have proceeded effortlessly through accounts payable without further scrutiny. Of course, the authorized approver is the fraudster, which illustrates yet again the need for two tiers of approval on any significant transaction."
